{{notability|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox military person |name=Willy Tscherning |birth_date=15 June 1917 |death_date={{death date and age|2012|1|20|1917|6|17|df=y}} |image= |caption= |birth_place= [[Naumburg (Saale)|Naumburg]] |death_place= [[Borna, Leipzig|Borna]] |allegiance={{flag|Nazi Germany}} |branch={{Luftwaffe}} |serviceyears=1936–45 |rank=[[Oberfeldwebel]] |unit=[[KG 1|Kampfgeschwader 1]] |commands= |battles=[[World War II]] *[[Invasion of Poland]] *[[Battle of France]] *[[Battle of Britain]] *[[Operation Barbarossa]] *[[Siege of Leningrad]] *[[Battle of Stalingrad]] *[[Demyansk Pocket]] *[[Battle of Kursk]] *[[Operation Bagration]] |awards=[[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] |laterwork=}}
'''Willy Tscherning''' (15 June 1917 – 20 January 2012) was a highly decorated [[Oberfeldwebel]] in the [[Luftwaffe]] during [[World War II]]. He was also a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership. Willy Tscherning was captured by American forces on 6 May 1945, and was released from captivity on 1 May 1946.
==Awards== * [[Aviator badge|Flugzeugführerabzeichen]] * [[Front Flying Clasp of the Luftwaffe]] in Gold * [[Ehrenpokal der Luftwaffe]] (9 February 1942) * [[Iron Cross]] (1939) ** 2nd Class ** 1st Class * [[German Cross]] in Gold on 21 August 1942 as ''[[Feldwebel]]'' in the 3./Kampfgeschwader 1<ref>Patzwall & Scherzer 2001, p. 481.</ref> * [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] on 18 November 1944 as ''[[Oberfeldwebel]]'' and ''Bordfunker'' (aerial radio operator) in the 9./Kampfgeschwader 1 "Hindenburg"<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 346.</ref>
